# Production Master — canonical agent policy

The single source of truth for how agents work in this repo is **`AGENTS.md`** at the
repo root. Read it before making any change.

Key points it enforces (see `AGENTS.md` for the full, authoritative text):

- This repo is a **thin client** over the hosted service — presentation and transport
  only. **All investigation logic is server-side and never lives here.**
- **No LLM/provider SDK imports** and **no server-side pipeline logic** — CI grep-enforces
  both (the ip-guard job).
- Host-neutral `plugin-core`; IDE-specific code only in `adapter-*` packages.
- CI runs on GitHub-hosted `ubuntu-latest` only; no secrets in code/config.
- Conventional Commits, `feat/`|`fix/` branches, squash-merge, green CI before merge.

Do not fork policy into this file — edit `AGENTS.md` instead.
